WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:29.104 --> 00:00:31.357
Howdy there. Mr. Lee.

3
00:00:31.523 --> 00:00:33.776
What's this? Filipino New Year's?

4
00:00:34.360 --> 00:00:35.945
No. Why you say that?

5
00:00:36.028 --> 00:00:37.863
'Cause you're cooking a feast.

6
00:00:37.947 --> 00:00:40.449
I can smell it from the interstate.

7
00:00:40.783 --> 00:00:43.035
What is that? Barbecue?

8
00:00:43.244 --> 00:00:45.746
Yeah. But it not coming from here.

9
00:00:46.622 --> 00:00:48.249
What is that noise?

10
00:04:19.631 --> 00:04:22.217
What is your take on this. Jerry?

11
00:04:22.759 --> 00:04:25.261
The people will love it. Mr. President.

12
00:04:25.595 --> 00:04:30.183
Our conflict is whether we ambush
the 6:00 news or hold out for prime time.

13
00:04:30.350 --> 00:04:32.685
Screw the press.
This is a need-to-know situation.

14
00:04:32.769 --> 00:04:36.773
We should make it top secret.
and should move in with Defcon Four.

15
00:04:36.981 --> 00:04:38.858
We can't sit on this.

16
00:04:40.526 --> 00:04:42.987
General Casey. do you have an opinion?

17
00:04:44.364 --> 00:04:45.615
Well. sir...

18
00:04:45.782 --> 00:04:47.283
...do we know they are hostile?

19
00:04:47.367 --> 00:04:49.285
What do you mean?

20
00:04:49.702 --> 00:04:52.288
They have the planet surrounded
by thousands of warships!

21
00:04:52.372 --> 00:04:54.290
Do we know they're warships?

22
00:04:57.794 --> 00:05:00.880
Professor. what do we know about them?

23
00:05:02.550 --> 00:05:04.718
They're very advanced technologically.

24
00:05:04.802 --> 00:05:08.055
Which suggests. rightfully so.
that they're peaceful.

25
00:05:08.639 --> 00:05:13.018
An advanced civilization is.
by definition. not barbaric.

26
00:05:13.143 --> 00:05:14.645
Mr. President...

27
00:05:15.020 --> 00:05:16.564
...this is a great day.

28
00:05:16.647 --> 00:05:18.649
I and all my colleagues...

29
00:05:18.816 --> 00:05:20.568
...are extremely excited.

30
00:05:21.026 --> 00:05:21.944
Good.

31
00:05:23.153 --> 00:05:25.531
Extraterrestrial life.

32
00:05:26.657 --> 00:05:28.325
You're right. Jerry.

33
00:05:28.534 --> 00:05:31.036
The people are going to love it.

34
00:05:31.161 --> 00:05:33.539
This is a momentous occasion.

35
00:05:34.415 --> 00:05:35.249
Mr. President--

36
00:05:35.332 --> 00:05:37.167
We'll go all media on this.

37
00:05:37.334 --> 00:05:39.086
I'll wear my Cerruti suit.

38
00:05:39.253 --> 00:05:40.921
I'll need a good speech.

39
00:05:41.922 --> 00:05:43.340
Statesman-like...

40
00:05:43.674 --> 00:05:45.384
...historical and yet...

41
00:05:45.593 --> 00:05:47.595
...warm. neighborly.

42
00:05:47.761 --> 00:05:51.557
Abraham Lincoln meets
Leave it to Beaver. kind of thing.

43
00:05:53.058 --> 00:05:54.685
Are they too old-fashioned?

44
00:05:54.768 --> 00:05:56.353
No. I don't think so.

45
00:05:56.604 --> 00:06:00.065
This has got the colors but. no.
I don't think so.

46
00:06:00.191 --> 00:06:01.568
Not vivid enough.

47
00:06:01.776 --> 00:06:03.778
Nancy had this in the library.

48
00:06:03.945 --> 00:06:04.696
Yes. indeed.

49
00:06:04.779 --> 00:06:06.031
I don't think so.

50
00:06:06.114 --> 00:06:09.492
I thought perhaps the watered silk.
This week it's on sale.

51
00:06:09.868 --> 00:06:12.579
I hardly think I need worry about that.

52
00:06:12.704 --> 00:06:15.373
My husband is the leader of the free world.

53
00:06:16.583 --> 00:06:18.043
What do you think?

54
00:06:18.710 --> 00:06:22.756
Why don't you leave the Roosevelt Room
the way the Roosevelts wanted it.

55
00:06:23.465 --> 00:06:27.719
Because Eleanor Roosevelt was
too fond of chintz. That's why.

56
00:06:28.136 --> 00:06:30.222
Mother. this isn't your house.

57
00:06:30.388 --> 00:06:33.475
lf you're going to be a pest. I'll ignore you!

58
00:06:33.725 --> 00:06:34.851
Mrs. Dale?

59
00:06:57.290 --> 00:06:59.960
I saw you fight Sonny Liston in '69.

60
00:07:00.127 --> 00:07:01.212
Really?

61
00:07:01.379 --> 00:07:03.548
You were a nun back then?

62
00:07:03.714 --> 00:07:06.884
We've always been fight fans.
haven't we sisters?

63
00:07:07.218 --> 00:07:09.470
Byron Williams. telephone.

64
00:07:09.637 --> 00:07:10.721
I must go.

65
00:07:10.888 --> 00:07:13.391
You ladies have a nice time.

66
00:07:19.021 --> 00:07:20.356
Oh. Louise.

67
00:07:20.898 --> 00:07:23.067
Sorry to call you at work. but...

68
00:07:23.568 --> 00:07:27.738
...the boys haven't been home
in two nights. I don't know what to do.

69
00:07:27.905 --> 00:07:29.991
You're doing the best you can.

70
00:07:30.241 --> 00:07:31.993
They're just at that age.

71
00:07:34.078 --> 00:07:37.540
The casino manager's giving me
the evil eye. I've gotta go.

72
00:07:37.665 --> 00:07:39.417
I'll call you later. okay?

73
00:07:40.251 --> 00:07:43.421
Are you still cool on me
coming to Washington?

74
00:07:43.588 --> 00:07:45.256
'Course I am.

75
00:07:45.756 --> 00:07:48.342
You take care. okay? Bye.

76
00:08:04.276 --> 00:08:06.111
Must you drink in front of me?

77
00:08:06.194 --> 00:08:08.280
You're an adult. Just cope.

78
00:08:08.447 --> 00:08:11.617
It doesn't help me
that all we ever do is sit in bars.

79
00:08:11.783 --> 00:08:13.619
This is work. baby. okay?

80
00:08:13.785 --> 00:08:17.456
I'm checking the decor.
the lighting. the traffic flow.

81
00:08:17.623 --> 00:08:20.626
lf I'd known you'd turn into a crook.
I wouldn't have married you.

82
00:08:20.709 --> 00:08:22.628
I'm not a crook.

83
00:08:22.794 --> 00:08:24.963
I'm ambitious. There's a difference.

84
00:08:25.047 --> 00:08:27.799
lf you think you can make
a nickel in this town...

85
00:08:27.883 --> 00:08:31.637
...without knowing how to dally
around a few curves. well...

86
00:08:31.970 --> 00:08:34.640
...you know nothing
of the gambling industry.

87
00:08:36.141 --> 00:08:40.229
The Galaxy's going to be
the best hotel in Vegas.

88
00:08:40.395 --> 00:08:42.064
The best!

89
00:08:42.272 --> 00:08:43.148
I promise.

90
00:08:43.232 --> 00:08:45.817
But don't you realize what you're doing?
You're destroying the Earth!

91
00:08:45.901 --> 00:08:48.820
All this greed! This money system!

92
00:08:48.987 --> 00:08:51.156
You're destroying everything!

93
00:08:51.907 --> 00:08:53.825
Okay. Barbara. okay.

94
00:08:54.159 --> 00:08:56.245
Keep your voice down.

95
00:08:56.995 --> 00:08:58.997
I got friends here.

96
00:09:00.333 --> 00:09:01.292
Sugar!

97
00:09:01.668 --> 00:09:03.086
Hit me one more time.

98
00:09:03.169 --> 00:09:04.587
Stop flirting with the waitress.

99
00:09:04.671 --> 00:09:06.005
God. Here.

100
00:09:07.590 --> 00:09:09.342
Go over to the roulette...

101
00:09:10.927 --> 00:09:12.679
...play our anniversary...

102
00:09:12.762 --> 00:09:14.847
...and stay off of black.

103
00:09:18.017 --> 00:09:18.851
Thanks.

104
00:09:27.402 --> 00:09:30.071
Make it quick.
we go out live in ten minutes.

105
00:09:30.905 --> 00:09:33.283
What? The actual president?

106
00:09:33.491 --> 00:09:34.659
Cutting in?

107
00:09:38.913 --> 00:09:42.083
Budget negotiations may be dead
in the water after this week.

108
00:09:42.166 --> 00:09:43.793
Hair looks good.

109
00:09:45.169 --> 00:09:46.254
I like the hair.

110
00:09:46.337 --> 00:09:48.506
...quote. ''factually-challenged. ''

111
00:09:49.340 --> 00:09:51.092
Yeah. Stone. Speak.

112
00:09:51.259 --> 00:09:52.760
Jason. hi. it's me.

113
00:09:53.928 --> 00:09:55.388
You wearing a bra?

114
00:09:55.847 --> 00:09:59.642
Listen. this is big. President Dale
is cutting into my show today.

115
00:10:01.270 --> 00:10:04.148
That's absurd. Why would he stoop
to being on ''Today in Fashion''?

116
00:10:04.231 --> 00:10:05.691
He's interrupting everybody.

117
00:10:05.774 --> 00:10:09.194
I don't know. it's some sort of
an emergency announcement.

118
00:10:09.361 --> 00:10:12.072
This doesn't make sense.
He should talk to us.

119
00:10:13.115 --> 00:10:15.159
White House is coming out live.

120
00:10:16.118 --> 00:10:18.954
Good evening. my fellow Americans.

121
00:10:19.288 --> 00:10:22.958
I apologize for interrupting
your regular programs...

122
00:10:23.125 --> 00:10:26.128
...but I have a very important
announcement to make.

123
00:10:26.629 --> 00:10:29.715
Many important things have happened
to me in my life:

124
00:10:30.216 --> 00:10:32.468
My graduation from Princeton...

125
00:10:32.968 --> 00:10:36.472
...the day that Marsha said
she would be my wife...

126
00:10:36.639 --> 00:10:38.891
...the birth of our daughter Taffy.

127
00:10:39.058 --> 00:10:40.059
Thanks. Dad.

128
00:10:40.142 --> 00:10:44.813
And the news that I have heard today
ranks right up there.

129
00:10:45.064 --> 00:10:47.316
A powerful memory is in the making.

130
00:10:47.983 --> 00:10:49.735
Not just for me...

131
00:10:49.902 --> 00:10:51.737
...but for all mankind.

132
00:10:52.029 --> 00:10:53.030
Today...

133
00:10:53.072 --> 00:10:56.659
...an extraordinary discovery
was made by the Hubble telescope.

134
00:10:58.787 --> 00:11:01.706
The data from the Hubble was decoded...

135
00:11:02.541 --> 00:11:07.170
...then analyzed by the most
powerful computers at MIT.

136
00:11:07.796 --> 00:11:10.048
The images are undeniable.

137
00:11:10.549 --> 00:11:13.718
We are entering the dawn of a new era.

138
00:11:14.886 --> 00:11:18.723
Frame enlargements provide
an astonishing sight.

139
00:11:18.974 --> 00:11:23.562
A fleet of vehicles.
which can best be described as...

140
00:11:23.812 --> 00:11:25.397
...flying saucers.

141
00:11:25.564 --> 00:11:28.733
Come on! Come on!
Papa needs a new pair of shoes!

142
00:11:31.736 --> 00:11:34.406
Hey. am I the only one
shooting craps here?

143
00:11:34.573 --> 00:11:38.285
We hope we will have the chance
to meet with them.

144
00:11:38.451 --> 00:11:41.204
This is the perfect summation
to the 20th Century....

145
00:11:41.288 --> 00:11:42.706
Martians.

146
00:11:43.290 --> 00:11:45.208
This is great.

147
00:11:45.625 --> 00:11:48.378
Please. come to Earth. Please.

148
00:11:49.045 --> 00:11:50.380
We need you.

149
00:11:54.551 --> 00:11:56.636
I got people coming in!

150
00:11:56.803 --> 00:11:59.639
Everybody wants to be part of this.

151
00:11:59.724 --> 00:12:02.560
Galaxy's going to be world class.

152
00:12:03.644 --> 00:12:04.979
And soon...

153
00:12:05.146 --> 00:12:08.149
...we will become one solar system.

154
00:12:08.649 --> 00:12:09.984
What the hell's he talking about?

155
00:12:10.067 --> 00:12:12.653
These flying saucers
have come from Mars...

156
00:12:14.405 --> 00:12:16.991
...and at their current course and speed...

157
00:12:17.325 --> 00:12:18.993
...will enter Earth's orbit in 16 hours.

158
00:12:19.076 --> 00:12:22.997
I've been thinking about Martians
when there weren't any.

159
00:12:23.414 --> 00:12:28.002
It is profoundly moving to know
there is intelligent life out there.

160
00:12:28.169 --> 00:12:29.670
Glad it's somewhere.

161
00:12:29.754 --> 00:12:33.591
Our world
will never feel quite the same again.

162
00:12:35.176 --> 00:12:36.427
Good night...

163
00:12:37.428 --> 00:12:39.305
...and God bless you all.

164
00:12:49.857 --> 00:12:51.192
This...

165
00:12:52.109 --> 00:12:53.694
...is intense.

166
00:12:56.364 --> 00:12:58.449
Shut up. Poppy. Shut up.

167
00:12:59.534 --> 00:13:00.869
Shut up!

168
00:13:01.536 --> 00:13:02.746
Jason Stone.

169
00:13:05.624 --> 00:13:06.875
It's for you.

170
00:13:08.710 --> 00:13:11.213
Poppy. honey. No. sweetie.

171
00:13:12.881 --> 00:13:15.050
That's right. Good girl.

172
00:13:18.971 --> 00:13:20.597
I could be there at...

173
00:13:21.223 --> 00:13:23.225
...I don't know. 11:00.

174
00:13:38.657 --> 00:13:42.160
They want me to interview
the professor from the White House.

175
00:13:42.828 --> 00:13:43.870
Kessler?

176
00:13:45.497 --> 00:13:46.582
Donald Kessler?

177
00:13:46.665 --> 00:13:48.709
Yeah. I think that was his name.

178
00:13:49.543 --> 00:13:50.919
You know. the science guy.

179
00:13:51.003 --> 00:13:52.838
This is nuts. this is....

180
00:13:53.171 --> 00:13:55.090
We should have got that guy.

181
00:13:55.507 --> 00:13:57.676
Your people are too slow.

182
00:13:59.012 --> 00:14:00.263
Right. Poppy?

183
00:14:24.120 --> 00:14:25.121
Finished!

184
00:14:25.204 --> 00:14:27.040
One minute. 57 seconds.

185
00:14:28.541 --> 00:14:30.793
-Didn't I tell you under two minutes?
-You did!

186
00:14:30.877 --> 00:14:31.878
You did!

187
00:14:31.961 --> 00:14:33.046
Hot damn.

188
00:14:33.796 --> 00:14:35.173
Want a doughnut?

189
00:14:35.465 --> 00:14:36.549
How old are they?

190
00:14:36.633 --> 00:14:38.051
Fresh baked. Monday.

191
00:14:38.134 --> 00:14:40.803
Richie. that's six days ago!

192
00:14:41.304 --> 00:14:42.722
Give me a couple.

193
00:14:46.476 --> 00:14:48.895
This Martian thing is pretty awesome.

194
00:14:49.062 --> 00:14:52.815
Did one of you traitors see my Muffy?

195
00:14:52.982 --> 00:14:54.734
Your brother's volunteering.

196
00:14:54.817 --> 00:14:56.986
As soon as I get back to the base.

197
00:14:57.070 --> 00:14:58.321
Volunteer for what?

198
00:14:58.405 --> 00:14:59.907
Martian detail.

199
00:15:00.991 --> 00:15:01.825
Cool.

200
00:15:01.909 --> 00:15:05.496
lf any Martians come around here.
I'll kick their butts!

201
00:15:17.925 --> 00:15:18.926
Jump!

202
00:15:28.477 --> 00:15:30.980
Folks.
we must make an unscheduled stop!

203
00:15:34.358 --> 00:15:35.526
It's Mama.

204
00:15:36.277 --> 00:15:39.530
Why are you here?
lf you ain't home. why ain't you in class?

205
00:15:39.613 --> 00:15:40.698
Class was cancelled.

206
00:15:40.781 --> 00:15:42.199
It was not!

207
00:15:42.366 --> 00:15:43.367
-Come here!
-Why?

208
00:15:43.450 --> 00:15:45.244
I'm not going to hurt you.

209
00:15:45.703 --> 00:15:46.954
Let go of him.

210
00:15:48.539 --> 00:15:50.958
Okay. Now just come here.

211
00:15:51.292 --> 00:15:52.543
Come here.

212
00:15:53.794 --> 00:15:55.462
Think it's smart to cut school?

213
00:15:55.546 --> 00:15:57.464
-What are you doing?
-Do you?

214
00:15:58.466 --> 00:15:59.634
No. it's dumb.

215
00:15:59.718 --> 00:16:01.553
You'll flunk! Go to jail!

216
00:16:01.720 --> 00:16:03.555
Get on the bus!

217
00:16:03.722 --> 00:16:04.806
Get on!

218
00:16:05.056 --> 00:16:07.559
I'll be tripping on you. Get back there.

219
00:16:07.726 --> 00:16:09.311
I don't want to hear anymore.

220
00:16:09.394 --> 00:16:10.478
I hate school.

221
00:16:10.562 --> 00:16:11.813
I heard that!

222
00:16:35.670 --> 00:16:36.755
Hi. there.

223
00:16:36.838 --> 00:16:38.006
Want a date?

224
00:16:38.173 --> 00:16:39.591
How about it?

225
00:16:39.841 --> 00:16:41.176
A date?

226
00:16:43.511 --> 00:16:44.804
It sounds good.

227
00:16:47.015 --> 00:16:48.850
The stress at work is...

228
00:16:49.184 --> 00:16:50.769
...unbelievable.

229
00:16:56.233 --> 00:16:57.984
May I speak to you in private?

230
00:16:58.069 --> 00:17:00.863
No. I must watch the floor.
What do you want?

231
00:17:01.364 --> 00:17:04.992
-I'm supporting a family back east.
-I thought you were divorced.

232
00:17:05.076 --> 00:17:07.870
I am. but I still have to take care of them.

233
00:17:08.746 --> 00:17:11.874
Things have been a little lean around here.

234
00:17:12.041 --> 00:17:14.001
I was wondering if I could get a raise?

235
00:17:14.085 --> 00:17:15.294
Out of the question.

236
00:17:15.378 --> 00:17:18.589
I'm an asset to this hotel.
They like me around here.

237
00:17:18.756 --> 00:17:20.424
You're a nice guy.

238
00:17:20.758 --> 00:17:24.595
But I can get Leon Spinks
or Buster Douglas for the same money.

239
00:17:25.054 --> 00:17:27.932
You better get moving.
You're on in five minutes.

240
00:17:37.108 --> 00:17:39.610
This show's going to get a great rating.

241
00:17:40.403 --> 00:17:41.696
It's all yours.

242
00:17:42.613 --> 00:17:47.577
ln certain circumstances the proposition
that two and two equals five...

243
00:17:47.743 --> 00:17:49.579
...is entirely legitimate.

244
00:17:51.289 --> 00:17:52.707
Call me Nathalie.

245
00:17:53.124 --> 00:17:55.918
And you. do please call me Donald.

246
00:17:57.296 --> 00:17:58.797
I admire your show.

247
00:18:01.258 --> 00:18:03.760
Really? You like my work?

248
00:18:04.136 --> 00:18:06.096
Yes. Very much.

249
00:18:06.263 --> 00:18:07.598
Why....

250
00:18:08.140 --> 00:18:09.933
Thank you.

251
00:18:10.100 --> 00:18:11.852
Coming out of commercial.

252
00:18:11.935 --> 00:18:13.645
In five...four...

253
00:18:13.812 --> 00:18:15.480
...three...two....

254
00:18:15.564 --> 00:18:18.984
Welcome back.
We're with Professor Donald Kessler.

255
00:18:20.944 --> 00:18:24.114
He's the chairman
of the American Academy...

256
00:18:24.281 --> 00:18:26.658
...of Astronautics.

257
00:18:27.826 --> 00:18:29.161
Professor...

258
00:18:29.453 --> 00:18:32.831
...isn't it weird that we sent
a space probe to Mars...

259
00:18:32.998 --> 00:18:35.083
...and we didn't even find anyone?

260
00:18:35.167 --> 00:18:37.169
Well. not really...

261
00:18:37.336 --> 00:18:38.545
...Nathalie.

262
00:18:39.004 --> 00:18:41.340
We didn't get into the canals.

263
00:18:41.506 --> 00:18:43.550
The Martian canals are canyons.

264
00:18:43.800 --> 00:18:45.969
Some are over 100 miles deep.

265
00:18:46.178 --> 00:18:51.016
The Martian civilization has clearly
developed under the planet's surface.

266
00:18:51.350 --> 00:18:54.895
Their science and technology
must be absolutely mind-boggling.

267
00:18:55.687 --> 00:18:56.605
So...

268
00:18:56.688 --> 00:18:58.690
