538
00:42:31.794 --> 00:42:34.380
No. it ain't happening! It didn't happen!

539
00:43:31.230 --> 00:43:33.398
Holy Mother of God!

540
00:43:34.066 --> 00:43:35.525
Did you see that?

541
00:43:35.692 --> 00:43:39.154
We should hit these assholes
with everything we've got. sir.

542
00:43:39.738 --> 00:43:41.281
Sir. Mr. President.
I know this seems terrible...

543
00:43:41.365 --> 00:43:43.325
...but let's not be too rash.

544
00:43:43.408 --> 00:43:44.952
We should nuke them!

545
00:43:45.410 --> 00:43:48.205
We must establish
a line of communication first.

546
00:43:48.872 --> 00:43:50.582
Set up a town hall.

547
00:43:50.749 --> 00:43:52.793
We'll get the public's opinion.

548
00:43:54.754 --> 00:43:56.547
What do you think?

549
00:43:58.258 --> 00:44:00.051
Kick the crap out of them.

550
00:44:01.552 --> 00:44:03.179
Ladies and gentlemen...

551
00:44:03.263 --> 00:44:05.807
...it may be a cultural misunderstanding.

552
00:44:06.557 --> 00:44:08.560
Maybe to them. doves mean war.

553
00:44:10.478 --> 00:44:13.481
We all saw how they reacted to that dove.

554
00:44:13.815 --> 00:44:15.316
It frightened them.

555
00:44:15.733 --> 00:44:17.902
He did say that...

556
00:44:19.904 --> 00:44:22.073
...''We come in peace.''

557
00:44:31.916 --> 00:44:34.002
The new computer's ready.

558
00:44:34.168 --> 00:44:36.170
Okay. let's do it.

559
00:44:36.337 --> 00:44:38.923
I know we're making the right decision.

560
00:44:41.926 --> 00:44:43.428
Ready to transmit.

561
00:44:45.513 --> 00:44:49.267
This is the president of the United States.

562
00:44:50.184 --> 00:44:52.020
I'm speaking in the hope...

563
00:44:52.186 --> 00:44:55.565
...that what happened earlier today
in the Nevada desert...

564
00:44:55.941 --> 00:44:59.111
...was a cultural misunderstanding.

565
00:44:59.945 --> 00:45:02.865
There can be no doubt
that we two peoples...

566
00:45:03.032 --> 00:45:06.285
...have a great deal to offer one another.

567
00:45:06.452 --> 00:45:08.454
You must be as excited as we...

568
00:45:08.621 --> 00:45:11.832
...to find intelligent life in the solar system.

569
00:45:12.958 --> 00:45:14.877
Let me make it clear.

570
00:45:15.044 --> 00:45:16.712
You have nothing...

571
00:45:16.879 --> 00:45:18.881
...to fear from us.

572
00:45:19.298 --> 00:45:22.468
Our customs may be strange to you...

573
00:45:22.635 --> 00:45:25.304
...but we mean no harm.

574
00:46:37.294 --> 00:46:39.879
When the investors fly in...

575
00:46:40.380 --> 00:46:43.049
...I would like for them each to be...

576
00:46:44.384 --> 00:46:45.885
...met by a limo.

577
00:46:46.886 --> 00:46:49.306
Top of the line cars...

578
00:46:49.889 --> 00:46:52.225
...leather interiors...

579
00:46:52.809 --> 00:46:55.228
...Corinthian. if they got it.

580
00:46:56.063 --> 00:46:59.483
Are you still spinning your wheels
on that cockamamie hotel?

581
00:47:00.902 --> 00:47:02.153
Hello!

582
00:47:02.820 --> 00:47:04.822
The Martians have attacked!

583
00:47:04.989 --> 00:47:09.076
This was no misunderstanding.
I was there. I saw it.

584
00:47:09.243 --> 00:47:11.662
Look. you're worried about yesterday.

585
00:47:11.996 --> 00:47:13.998
I'm worried about tomorrow.

586
00:47:14.165 --> 00:47:17.752
The Martians land on Earth.
they'll need a place to stay.

587
00:47:17.919 --> 00:47:19.629
Just like everyone else.

588
00:47:20.421 --> 00:47:21.923
My God.

589
00:47:23.257 --> 00:47:26.010
Maybe we should all be destroyed.

590
00:47:27.011 --> 00:47:30.181
The human race doesn't deserve to live.

591
00:47:37.188 --> 00:47:38.356
Ethel...

592
00:47:38.522 --> 00:47:40.274
...that reminds me.

593
00:47:40.441 --> 00:47:42.860
I'd like the limos to be stocked...

594
00:47:43.027 --> 00:47:46.113
...with every kind of alcohol
known to man.

595
00:47:46.280 --> 00:47:49.033
And top it off with a bottle of Dom...

596
00:47:49.200 --> 00:47:50.701
...on ice.

597
00:47:51.702 --> 00:47:54.956
What confounds me most of all
is the lack of genitalia.

598
00:47:55.123 --> 00:47:57.042
Down here is the aorta.

599
00:47:57.209 --> 00:47:59.711
Up here we have the sphinx.

600
00:48:00.045 --> 00:48:03.215
Notice the highly developed
nerve system here.

601
00:48:03.382 --> 00:48:06.885
This explains. of course.
the cerebral arteries.

602
00:48:07.052 --> 00:48:10.722
And if we notice down here.
behind the optic chiasm...

603
00:48:11.473 --> 00:48:13.558
...several glands....

604
00:48:17.312 --> 00:48:19.147
Very curious.

605
00:49:01.774 --> 00:49:06.362
''He who believes in me.
though he die. yet shall he live.

606
00:49:07.280 --> 00:49:11.284
''And whoever lives and believes in me
shall never die.''

607
00:49:12.452 --> 00:49:15.788
Billy-Glenn Norris gave his life
defending our country.

608
00:49:15.955 --> 00:49:17.874
Why did it have to be him?

609
00:49:18.041 --> 00:49:22.045
He's a true American hero.
May God rest his soul.

610
00:49:23.713 --> 00:49:25.548
Ready! Aim.

611
00:49:27.133 --> 00:49:28.134
Fire!

612
00:49:29.552 --> 00:49:30.637
Aim!

613
00:49:30.970 --> 00:49:32.055
Fire!

614
00:49:44.734 --> 00:49:45.944
Hello?

615
00:49:46.110 --> 00:49:49.489
Byron! Is everything all right?
You still coming tomorrow?

616
00:49:49.572 --> 00:49:53.076
Just try and stop me.
That plane arrives at 4:00 p.m.

617
00:49:53.284 --> 00:49:54.786
Are the kids there?

618
00:49:54.954 --> 00:49:56.288
Yeah. hold on.

619
00:49:59.458 --> 00:50:01.126
-Me first.
-No. me.

620
00:50:04.755 --> 00:50:05.547
Hey. Dad.

621
00:50:05.631 --> 00:50:07.633
Who's that? Neville?

622
00:50:08.300 --> 00:50:09.301
How are you?

623
00:50:09.385 --> 00:50:11.303
We're going to the White House.

624
00:50:11.387 --> 00:50:12.972
The White House?

625
00:50:13.138 --> 00:50:14.390
Yeah. tomorrow.

626
00:50:14.556 --> 00:50:16.558
-Give it back!
-Leave me alone.

627
00:50:16.725 --> 00:50:18.978
It's a school thing. like a tour.

628
00:50:19.144 --> 00:50:22.064
So you're still going to school
once in a while?

629
00:50:23.566 --> 00:50:24.984
Give me your ma again.

630
00:50:25.067 --> 00:50:26.068
Hold on.

631
00:50:26.151 --> 00:50:26.986
Mom.

632
00:50:27.236 --> 00:50:29.989
-You always get to the phone first.
-So what?

633
00:50:30.656 --> 00:50:32.241
I'm first to the game.

634
00:50:34.326 --> 00:50:37.413
Why are you wasting this phone time?
I'll see you tomorrow.

635
00:50:37.496 --> 00:50:40.082
But there's something
I want to say to you.

636
00:50:40.249 --> 00:50:42.668
Just 'cause I feel like saying it.

637
00:50:42.918 --> 00:50:44.128
What's that?

638
00:50:44.837 --> 00:50:46.255
I love you.

639
00:50:48.090 --> 00:50:49.925
I love you too. Byron.

640
00:50:50.092 --> 00:50:53.178
Now stop wasting money!
I'll see you tomorrow!

641
00:51:10.697 --> 00:51:12.198
They're responding.

642
00:51:15.535 --> 00:51:17.537
A message from the Martians.

643
00:51:19.956 --> 00:51:20.874
Really?

644
00:51:20.957 --> 00:51:23.043
They've issued a formal apology.

645
00:51:24.961 --> 00:51:27.047
This is great!

646
00:51:27.797 --> 00:51:29.716
I told you this would happen.

647
00:51:29.883 --> 00:51:34.054
The Martian ambassador feels terrible
and wants to speak to Congress.

648
00:51:34.220 --> 00:51:35.805
That's good. isn't it?

649
00:51:35.972 --> 00:51:37.474
You bet.

650
00:51:38.058 --> 00:51:40.393
It's a victory for our administration.

651
00:52:54.970 --> 00:52:56.555
Ladies and gentlemen.

652
00:52:56.722 --> 00:52:59.808
This is a proud day for all Americans.

653
00:53:00.392 --> 00:53:03.645
This is a hell of a photo-op. Jerry.

654
00:53:04.229 --> 00:53:06.398
Are you sure I shouldn't be there?

655
00:53:06.565 --> 00:53:10.319
The Secret Service don't want
the executive branch...

656
00:53:10.485 --> 00:53:13.572
...and the legislative branch
in the same room.

657
00:53:14.656 --> 00:53:17.659
The Martian ambassador
is going to say a few words.

658
00:53:18.243 --> 00:53:20.412
Come on down. Mr. Ambassador!

659
00:54:28.481 --> 00:54:30.191
Mr. Ambassador. please!

660
00:54:35.989 --> 00:54:36.990
Please!

661
00:54:37.240 --> 00:54:39.158
This doesn't make sense!

662
00:54:39.325 --> 00:54:41.327
It's not logical! It's not--

663
00:54:43.329 --> 00:54:45.081
Guess it wasn't the dove.

664
00:54:47.000 --> 00:54:47.917
Fire!

665
00:54:53.757 --> 00:54:55.759
They blew up Congress!

666
00:55:17.865 --> 00:55:19.950
Why'd they do that?

667
00:55:20.159 --> 00:55:23.037
Maybe they don't like the human being.

668
00:55:41.013 --> 00:55:42.514
Hello. gentlemen.

669
00:55:42.681 --> 00:55:44.850
Nice of you to come on...

670
00:55:45.017 --> 00:55:46.852
...such short notice.

671
00:55:47.770 --> 00:55:49.271
General Decker...

672
00:55:49.438 --> 00:55:51.857
...it seems I owe you an apology.

673
00:55:52.107 --> 00:55:54.777
We all make mistakes. Mr. President.

674
00:55:54.945 --> 00:55:56.863
Not anymore.

675
00:55:57.197 --> 00:56:00.367
We're going to take charge of this thing!

676
00:56:00.617 --> 00:56:02.994
Excellent. I have prepared the order.

677
00:56:03.703 --> 00:56:04.871
What's this?

678
00:56:04.955 --> 00:56:08.291
Your executive order for full use
of our nuclear deterrent.

679
00:56:11.962 --> 00:56:14.547
Are you crazy? I'm not starting a war!

680
00:56:14.714 --> 00:56:18.802
We're already at war. sir! We have
to nuke them! We must nuke them now!

681
00:56:20.053 --> 00:56:23.473
General Decker. if you do not shut up...

682
00:56:23.890 --> 00:56:26.142
...I'll relieve you of your command.

683
00:56:26.309 --> 00:56:28.144
We must strike now. sir!

684
00:56:28.311 --> 00:56:30.313
Annihilate! Kill! Kill!

685
00:56:30.814 --> 00:56:31.815
Shut up!

686
00:56:31.982 --> 00:56:34.234
Shut up! Shut up!

687
00:56:59.927 --> 00:57:01.095
Now...

688
00:57:02.930 --> 00:57:05.433
...I want the people to know...

689
00:57:05.600 --> 00:57:08.853
...that they still have two out of three
branches of government...

690
00:57:08.936 --> 00:57:11.606
...working for them. and that ain't bad.

691
00:57:11.772 --> 00:57:16.694
I want the people to know
that the schools will still be open. okay?

692
00:57:17.278 --> 00:57:19.614
And I want the people to know...

693
00:57:19.780 --> 00:57:22.867
...that the garbage will still be carried out.

694
00:57:23.034 --> 00:57:24.702
And I want a cop...

695
00:57:24.869 --> 00:57:26.287
...on every corner.

696
00:57:26.370 --> 00:57:28.205
Which. incidentally...

697
00:57:28.372 --> 00:57:30.708
...we would already have...

698
00:57:30.875 --> 00:57:33.878
...if they had listened to me
in the last election.

699
00:57:37.048 --> 00:57:38.382
Jerry...

700
00:57:38.549 --> 00:57:40.718
...how soon can we go on the air?

701
00:57:46.223 --> 00:57:48.726
My fellow Americans.

702
00:57:49.226 --> 00:57:51.395
It is with a heavy heart...

703
00:57:51.562 --> 00:57:53.981
...that I speak to you this afternoon.

704
00:57:54.149 --> 00:57:55.400
As you know...

705
00:57:55.484 --> 00:58:00.405
...earlier today the Martian ambassador
and his confederates...

706
00:58:00.656 --> 00:58:02.407
...attacked and killed...

707
00:58:02.574 --> 00:58:06.745
...many of your representatives
on Capitol Hill.

708
00:58:07.329 --> 00:58:12.000
I will be conferring
with other world leaders as time goes on.

709
00:58:12.751 --> 00:58:16.672
And rest assured that. working together...

710
00:58:17.089 --> 00:58:19.758
...we will soon come out...

711
00:58:20.676 --> 00:58:23.595
...at a very real outcome.

712
00:58:25.847 --> 00:58:27.266
Thank you.

713
00:58:56.296 --> 00:58:58.047
Nathalie. is that you?

714
00:58:58.798 --> 00:59:00.049
Yes.

715
00:59:00.216 --> 00:59:01.384
How're you?

716
00:59:03.428 --> 00:59:05.513
Not terribly good. I'm afraid.

717
00:59:07.390 --> 00:59:09.142
May I ask you a question?

718
00:59:11.978 --> 00:59:13.563
Of course you can.

719
00:59:14.731 --> 00:59:17.150
Were you flirting with me on the show?

720
00:59:17.400 --> 00:59:18.568
Because...

721
00:59:18.818 --> 00:59:20.236
...if you were...

722
00:59:20.320 --> 00:59:22.155
...I just want you to know...

723
00:59:22.238 --> 00:59:24.073
...that I liked it.

724
00:59:25.575 --> 00:59:26.826
You did?

725
00:59:26.993 --> 00:59:27.994
Really?

726
00:59:28.077 --> 00:59:31.497
Because. you know.
I've watched you on TV quite a bit and...

727
00:59:31.581 --> 00:59:32.957
...well. I've...

728
00:59:33.416 --> 00:59:36.419
...had something of
a schoolboycrush on you for...

729
00:59:36.586 --> 00:59:37.837
...oh. gosh...

730
00:59:38.004 --> 00:59:39.255
...ages.

731
01:00:20.381 --> 01:00:21.507
Hi. there.

732
01:00:21.715 --> 01:00:24.134
Are you interested in the White House?

733
01:00:29.306 --> 01:00:31.809
I work there. I'm the press secretary.

734
01:00:31.976 --> 01:00:33.143
Jerry Ross.

735
01:00:33.894 --> 01:00:35.688
Have you ever heard of me?

736
01:00:37.314 --> 01:00:39.942
You wouldn't believe
the pressure of my job.

737
01:00:41.652 --> 01:00:43.821
It's nice to see a new face.

738
01:00:51.579 --> 01:00:52.997
Are you doing anything?

739
01:00:53.081 --> 01:00:55.166
'Cause if you want. I...

740
01:00:55.333 --> 01:00:57.377
...could give you a personalized tour.

741
01:00:57.460 --> 01:00:59.004
Would you like that?

742
01:01:01.381 --> 01:01:04.467
Hey. Mitch. it's me. Can you let me in?

743
01:01:08.305 --> 01:01:10.557
Hello. Mr. Ross. Sure.

744
01:01:10.724 --> 01:01:13.226
We're a little nervous here.
after what happened.

745
01:01:13.310 --> 01:01:14.394
Exactly.

746
01:01:23.737 --> 01:01:26.656
Many great men and women
have passed through here.

747
01:01:27.240 --> 01:01:29.409
Now we're passing through here.

748
01:01:29.910 --> 01:01:31.995
Feels good. don't it?

749
01:01:35.332 --> 01:01:37.167
You're very graceful.

750
01:01:37.918 --> 01:01:39.169
I like that.

751
01:01:46.843 --> 01:01:48.011
Come here.

752
01:02:08.532 --> 01:02:10.618
We call this the Kennedy Room.

753
01:02:14.956 --> 01:02:16.624
Pretty nifty. huh?

754
01:02:49.907 --> 01:02:51.158
So...

755
01:02:51.325 --> 01:02:52.910
...how about a drink?

756
01:03:23.025 --> 01:03:24.943
Getting more comfortable.

757
01:03:27.279 --> 01:03:28.697
Outstanding.

758
01:03:43.211 --> 01:03:44.796
How's my lady doing?

759
01:03:55.141 --> 01:03:57.226
Oh. missy. you're hot.

760
01:03:57.977 --> 01:04:00.396
Could we get that gum out of your mouth?

761
01:04:06.986 --> 01:04:08.321
My finger!

762
01:04:13.493 --> 01:04:16.329
Hello! Hello. operator?
This is an emergency!

763
01:04:16.496 --> 01:04:17.580
Help!

764
01:05:43.417 --> 01:05:44.585
Don't shoot!

765
01:05:49.089 --> 01:05:50.674
Don't worry. darling.

766
01:05:59.517 --> 01:06:00.602
Get down!

767
01:06:10.946 --> 01:06:12.364
Thank you. Mitch.

768
01:06:12.530 --> 01:06:13.740
It's my job.

769
01:07:08.004 --> 01:07:08.921
What's happening?

770
01:07:09.005 --> 01:07:12.425
They appear to be
in a highly agitated state.

771
01:07:12.592 --> 01:07:15.011
And I. I don't know.

772
01:07:15.678 --> 01:07:17.263
I honestly don't know.

773
01:07:17.430 --> 01:07:20.433
I don't know what's going on anymore.
This is frustrating.

774
01:07:20.516 --> 01:07:22.226
I'm not feeling myself.

775
01:07:22.602 --> 01:07:24.687
lf only I could hold you in my arms!

776
01:07:24.770 --> 01:07:26.355
Oh. Donald!

777
01:07:26.522 --> 01:07:28.149
I'm scared!

778
01:08:02.309 --> 01:08:03.393
Excuse me.

779
01:08:03.560 --> 01:08:06.396
You said you wanted to know
as soon as possible.

780
01:08:06.563 --> 01:08:07.648
What is it?

781
01:08:07.731 --> 01:08:08.982
It's NO2.

782
01:08:09.149 --> 01:08:10.901
Highly concentrated.

783
01:08:11.068 --> 01:08:12.402
Nitrogen.

784
01:08:12.903 --> 01:08:14.237
So...

785
01:08:14.488 --> 01:08:17.491
...that's how it could breathe
in our atmosphere.

786
01:08:18.325 --> 01:08:20.160
What's that noise?

787
01:08:52.151 --> 01:08:55.321
But. Theodore.
I simply do not feel that Lincoln....

788
01:08:55.738 --> 01:08:57.407
It's a full-scale invasion.

789
01:08:57.490 --> 01:08:59.242
We must get you to safety.

790
01:09:05.164 --> 01:09:06.416
Not this way?

791
01:09:06.499 --> 01:09:09.002
I'm sorry. there's a tour going through.

792
01:09:09.586 --> 01:09:13.590
The Blue Room is often considered
the most beautiful in the White House.

793
01:09:13.756 --> 01:09:16.926
It is often used by the president
to receive guests.

794
01:09:17.760 --> 01:09:20.763
It is furnished to represent
the period of James Monroe.

795
01:09:20.847 --> 01:09:22.056
What's that?

796
01:09:22.473 --> 01:09:23.808
That...

797
01:09:23.975 --> 01:09:26.561
...is a portrait of James Monroe.

798
01:10:18.447 --> 01:10:19.949
We lost Taffy!

799
01:10:24.536 --> 01:10:28.123
Keep moving.
we must get you to the back stairs!

800
01:10:34.630 --> 01:10:36.548
The Nancy Reagan chandelier!

801
01:10:55.527 --> 01:10:58.530
What are you gawking at?
Get that president out of here!

802
01:11:04.911 --> 01:11:06.913
I personally guarantee...

803
01:11:07.330 --> 01:11:10.792
...that you will get a complete return
on your investment...

804
01:11:10.917 --> 01:11:12.919
...within five months.

805
01:11:13.086 --> 01:11:15.005
Mr. Land. excuse me.

806
01:11:15.171 --> 01:11:18.425
Just a second. Sheik Rakula.

807
01:11:20.427 --> 01:11:21.177
Now...

808
01:11:21.261 --> 01:11:25.432
...even in a time of so-called
intergalactic emergency...

809
01:11:26.600 --> 01:11:27.934
...the people...

810
01:11:28.101 --> 01:11:30.770
...still want to roll them bones!

811
01:11:32.272 --> 01:11:33.773
I believe--

812
01:11:34.274 --> 01:11:36.109
Just five more minutes.

813
01:11:37.027 --> 01:11:40.030
What I'd like for you to do is to...

814
01:11:40.196 --> 01:11:43.533
...view our new.
state-of-the-art show room.

815
01:11:44.868 --> 01:11:47.203
It is out-of-sight!

816
01:11:48.788 --> 01:11:49.915
Gentlemen.

817
01:11:53.961 --> 01:11:55.963
There is no way...

818
01:11:56.130 --> 01:11:57.965
...that we can lose.

819
01:12:43.177 --> 01:12:46.514
''It's not unusual to be loved by anyone

820
01:12:48.349 --> 01:12:51.936
''It's not unusual to have fun with anyone

821
01:12:53.438 --> 01:12:57.025
''But when I see you hanging
about with anyone

822
01:12:58.902 --> 01:13:01.571
''It's not unusual to see me cry

823
01:13:03.490 --> 01:13:05.492
''I want to die''

824
01:13:06.326 --> 01:13:08.161
I've called you all day.

825
01:13:08.328 --> 01:13:09.746
The flight's been canceled.

826
01:13:09.830 --> 01:13:12.332
Byron. there's Martians everywhere!

827
01:13:13.250 --> 01:13:14.209
Hello?

828
01:13:15.836 --> 01:13:17.254
I can't hear you!

829
01:13:22.884 --> 01:13:24.636
I must get to Washington.

830
01:13:29.725 --> 01:13:31.518
Do you know anyone who can fly a plane?

831
01:13:31.602 --> 01:13:32.769
Your husband. Art.

832
01:13:32.853 --> 01:13:33.937
He's dead.

833
01:13:34.104 --> 01:13:35.647
I told him this would happen.

834
01:13:35.731 --> 01:13:37.899
I loaded the plane with supplies.

835
01:13:38.191 --> 01:13:42.529
I want to go to the Tahoe caves.
It's remote. the Martians won't find it.

836
01:13:42.946 --> 01:13:43.947
Where's the plane?

837
01:13:44.031 --> 01:13:46.783
Private airfield. Other side of the freeway.

838
01:13:46.950 --> 01:13:48.702
Will it fly to Washington?

839
01:13:48.869 --> 01:13:50.704
I want to go to Tahoe.

840
01:13:50.871 --> 01:13:52.706
''You find it happens

841
01:13:52.874 --> 01:13:55.043
''All the time

842
01:13:55.627 --> 01:13:58.046
''Love will never do

843
01:13:58.713 --> 01:14:00.715
''What you want it to

844
01:14:01.633 --> 01:14:03.635
''Why can't this crazy love

845
01:14:04.052 --> 01:14:06.054
''Be mine''

846
01:14:14.979 --> 01:14:16.314
Jesus Christ!

847
01:14:25.365 --> 01:14:26.866
Girls. get out!

848
01:14:36.125 --> 01:14:38.544
There's a Martian right behind me!

849
01:14:38.711 --> 01:14:41.381
You're Tom Jones! ''It Ain't Unusual.''

850
01:14:42.548 --> 01:14:43.633
Autograph?

851
01:14:43.716 --> 01:14:45.843
Anybody got a pen?

852
01:15:03.988 --> 01:15:05.322
Great punch.

853
01:15:05.489 --> 01:15:06.907
You'll need that gun.

854
01:15:06.991 --> 01:15:08.742
-I'm Tom Jones.
-Byron Williams.

855
01:15:08.826 --> 01:15:11.078
I saw you fight in Cardiff. Wales.

856
01:15:12.413 --> 01:15:13.581
You okay?

857
01:15:13.998 --> 01:15:16.250
-I need a drink.
-You and me both.

858
01:15:16.417 --> 01:15:18.419
-We better go.
-Can you fly a plane?

859
01:15:18.502 --> 01:15:19.420
Sure. Got one?

860
01:15:19.503 --> 01:15:20.588
She has.

861
01:15:40.107 --> 01:15:42.860
Don't run. we are your friends.

862
01:16:13.892 --> 01:16:15.477
Martians blew up the shop!

863
01:16:15.560 --> 01:16:16.478
You're kidding.

864
01:16:16.561 --> 01:16:17.646
Should I get Grandma?

865
01:16:17.729 --> 01:16:21.232
Forget her! She's halfway
to outer space already! Here!

866
01:16:21.399 --> 01:16:24.569
I'll tell you one thing.
They ain't getting the TV!

867
01:16:28.239 --> 01:16:31.076
The president of France is on line two.

868
01:16:34.913 --> 01:16:38.166
Mr. President. the president of France
is on line two.

869
01:16:38.333 --> 01:16:40.168
He says it's important.

870
01:16:45.757 --> 01:16:47.926
Hello. Maurice.

871
01:16:50.595 --> 01:16:52.264
I have good news.

872
01:16:52.431 --> 01:16:53.933
The Martian ambassador is here.

873
01:16:54.016 --> 01:16:56.269
We've negotiated a settlement.

874
01:16:58.271 --> 01:17:00.606
Maurice get out of the room.

875
01:17:00.773 --> 01:17:02.275
Get out. now!

876
01:17:47.903 --> 01:17:49.155
Mr. President.

877
01:17:51.575 --> 01:17:53.327
Mr. President.

878
01:17:53.493 --> 01:17:56.079
I need you to sign this!

879
01:18:00.834 --> 01:18:02.336
What is it?

880
01:18:02.502 --> 01:18:04.922
My last will and testament?

881
01:18:05.088 --> 01:18:09.092
It is an order to deploy
our nuclear capability. sir.

882
01:19:20.915 --> 01:19:22.834
What the hell was that?

883
01:21:05.146 --> 01:21:06.064
Look!

884
01:21:13.488 --> 01:21:14.739
What was that?

885
01:21:16.783 --> 01:21:17.867
Where you going?

886
01:21:17.951 --> 01:21:19.035
To get Grandma.

887
01:21:19.119 --> 01:21:21.079
Stay and defend this trailer!

888
01:21:21.162 --> 01:21:23.290
That's what Billy-Glenn would do.

889
01:21:23.456 --> 01:21:25.041
You're disgracing a hero!

890
01:21:25.125 --> 01:21:27.627
I don't care. I'm gonna go get grandma.

891
01:21:28.295 --> 01:21:29.671
Come back here!

892
01:21:42.976 --> 01:21:44.728
What in the hell is that?

893
01:21:52.194 --> 01:21:53.529
Cut it out!

894
01:21:59.035 --> 01:22:00.411
Stop it!

895
01:22:09.337 --> 01:22:10.463
-This way!
-No. this way!

896
01:22:10.546 --> 01:22:13.007
It's a short cut! The airfield's--

897
01:22:13.174 --> 01:22:15.676
Bullshit! The airfield's over there!

898
01:22:21.515 --> 01:22:25.436
Being dressed like King Tut
doesn't make you our leader!

899
01:22:25.561 --> 01:22:27.063
Look. this is wrong!

900
01:22:27.229 --> 01:22:31.067
We're lost! He led us down a maze!
I'm going back to the hotel.

901
01:22:31.233 --> 01:22:32.568
-This way!
-Wait!

902
01:22:32.735 --> 01:22:34.570
Where are you going?

903
01:22:34.737 --> 01:22:35.488
Come on.

904
01:22:35.571 --> 01:22:37.073
But. I like him.

905
01:22:43.537 --> 01:22:47.875
Assholes! Why'd I listen to them?
I should have stayed in the hotel.

906
01:22:48.459 --> 01:22:49.877
Shit!

907
01:22:52.589 --> 01:22:54.091
I surrender. okay?

908
01:22:54.591 --> 01:22:56.885
You understand what that means?

909
01:22:58.095 --> 01:23:00.764
Look! You're intelligent beings.

910
01:23:01.390 --> 01:23:03.600
Let's cut a deal. I can help.

911
01:23:03.767 --> 01:23:05.227
I'm a lawyer!

912
01:23:05.560 --> 01:23:08.981
You want to conquer the world.
you'll need lawyers. right?

913
01:23:10.607 --> 01:23:11.608
Here.

914
01:23:12.484 --> 01:23:14.111
You want my watch?

915
01:23:14.611 --> 01:23:17.281
Take it. Take it. It's a Rolex!

916
01:23:27.791 --> 01:23:29.251
Nice shot!

917
01:23:29.418 --> 01:23:30.836
Pity I was too late.

918
01:23:30.919 --> 01:23:32.796
Can I have the gun back?

919
01:23:33.005 --> 01:23:34.923
Give me the gun and come on!

920
01:24:49.707 --> 01:24:50.708
Grandma!

921
01:24:59.093 --> 01:25:00.386
Oh. my God!

922
01:25:14.525 --> 01:25:16.902
I think these guys are very sick.

923
01:25:17.736 --> 01:25:20.447
What's happening to them?
What's killing them?

924
01:25:21.907 --> 01:25:24.285
I think it must be my music.

925
01:25:32.084 --> 01:25:33.502
Quiet!

926
01:26:25.138 --> 01:26:27.724
You think you can do anything you want.

927
01:26:27.891 --> 01:26:29.309
You can't.

928
01:26:29.476 --> 01:26:30.310
Because...

929
01:26:30.393 --> 01:26:32.646
...we are human...

930
01:26:32.979 --> 01:26:33.980
...beings.

931
01:26:34.064 --> 01:26:37.651
And we have the United States Army...

932
01:26:38.652 --> 01:26:40.236
...that'll fight you...

933
01:26:40.320 --> 01:26:44.407
...to the last man!
And we'll never surrender!

934
01:26:48.244 --> 01:26:49.829
Do you hear me?

935
01:26:49.997 --> 01:26:52.917
We'll fight you on the beaches.
We'll fight you in the streets.

936
01:26:53.000 --> 01:26:55.503
We will never. never surrender!

937
01:26:55.670 --> 01:26:58.005
We will win!

938
01:26:58.172 --> 01:27:00.007
Democracy will survive!

939
01:27:00.258 --> 01:27:02.093
We will never. ever...

940
01:27:02.260 --> 01:27:03.844
...surrender!

941
01:27:04.011 --> 01:27:05.346
We will win!

942
01:27:05.513 --> 01:27:07.515
The eagle will be triumphant!

943
01:27:37.545 --> 01:27:39.046
Why...

944
01:27:39.297 --> 01:27:41.048
...are you doing this?

945
01:27:43.134 --> 01:27:44.302
Why?

946
01:27:45.469 --> 01:27:48.222
lsn't the universe big enough...

947
01:27:48.806 --> 01:27:50.474
...for both of us?

948
01:27:54.396 --> 01:27:56.481
What is wrong with you people?

949
01:27:59.401 --> 01:28:01.069
We could work together.

950
01:28:02.237 --> 01:28:04.323
Why be enemies?

951
01:28:05.324 --> 01:28:07.075
Because we're different?

952
01:28:08.160 --> 01:28:09.828
Is that why?

953
01:28:13.999 --> 01:28:16.668
Think of the things that we could do.

954
01:28:18.086 --> 01:28:21.006
Think how strong we would be!

955
01:28:22.841 --> 01:28:24.343
Earth...

956
01:28:25.177 --> 01:28:27.095
...and Mars...

957
01:28:28.180 --> 01:28:29.431
...together.

958
01:28:32.059 --> 01:28:34.895
There is nothing
that we could not accomplish.

959
01:28:35.938 --> 01:28:37.689
Think about it!

960
01:28:39.942 --> 01:28:41.860
Think about it!

961
01:28:43.362 --> 01:28:45.030
Why destroy...

962
01:28:45.864 --> 01:28:48.033
...when you can create?

963
01:28:49.368 --> 01:28:51.370
We can have it all...

964
01:28:52.205 --> 01:28:54.624
...or we can smash it all!

965
01:28:58.127 --> 01:28:59.629
Why can't we...

966
01:28:59.879 --> 01:29:02.131
...work out our differences?

967
01:29:03.383 --> 01:29:05.301
Why can't we...

968
01:29:05.635 --> 01:29:07.804
...work things out?

969
01:29:10.306 --> 01:29:12.475
Little people...

970
01:29:14.811 --> 01:29:16.896
...why can't we all just...

971
01:29:18.147 --> 01:29:19.899
...get along?

972
01:29:46.759 --> 01:29:47.969
What's this?

973
01:30:26.216 --> 01:30:28.802
Don't run. We are your friends.

974
01:30:30.387 --> 01:30:32.973
Don't run. We are your friends.

975
01:30:46.445 --> 01:30:48.280
Next stop. radio station.

976
01:30:51.201 --> 01:30:52.702
There it is!

977
01:30:53.370 --> 01:30:54.955
Let's move it!

978
01:31:12.889 --> 01:31:14.224
There it is.

979
01:31:15.558 --> 01:31:17.644
Go start it. Go with him.

980
01:31:17.811 --> 01:31:19.396
Cindy. come with me.

981
01:31:36.663 --> 01:31:38.248
Are you sure you can fly this?

982
01:31:38.331 --> 01:31:40.000
I think so. yeah.

983
01:31:42.419 --> 01:31:43.837
Who put that on?

984
01:31:45.171 --> 01:31:47.924
-It's stuck!
-Cindy. over here.

985
01:31:54.432 --> 01:31:55.600
Shit!

986
01:31:56.517 --> 01:31:58.853
They haven't seen us yet. Come here.

987
01:32:00.938 --> 01:32:02.356
Get in the plane.

988
01:32:02.773 --> 01:32:04.609
I'll distract them.

989
01:32:04.775 --> 01:32:07.028
The first chance you get. go.

990
01:32:07.194 --> 01:32:09.363
-I'm not leaving you!
-Just do it!

991
01:32:09.447 --> 01:32:11.449
I'll draw them away! Go!

992
01:32:11.616 --> 01:32:12.700
No!

993
01:32:12.867 --> 01:32:14.285
I said go!

994
01:32:19.040 --> 01:32:20.625
Oh. my God!

995
01:32:21.459 --> 01:32:22.793
What's he doing?

996
01:32:22.877 --> 01:32:23.794
He's flipped!

997
01:32:23.878 --> 01:32:25.796
He's going to throw them off
so we can escape.

998
01:32:25.880 --> 01:32:27.381
We can't leave him!

999
01:32:30.551 --> 01:32:31.636
No weapon!

1000
01:32:31.969 --> 01:32:34.138
No clown outfit!

1001
01:32:34.305 --> 01:32:35.556
Just me!

1002
01:32:36.140 --> 01:32:37.558
Byron Williams...

1003
01:32:38.225 --> 01:32:40.478
...heavyweight champion...

1004
01:32:41.062 --> 01:32:42.730
...of the world!

1005
01:33:53.428 --> 01:33:55.513
Something's happened.

1006
01:33:55.805 --> 01:33:57.890
Something's happened to Byron.

1007
01:34:14.282 --> 01:34:16.868
''When I'm calling you

1008
01:34:38.473 --> 01:34:42.018
''That means I offer my love to you''

1009
01:35:19.431 --> 01:35:20.849
Good-bye. my darling.

1010
01:35:20.933 --> 01:35:22.893
I wish things were different.

1011
01:35:23.686 --> 01:35:25.354
So do I.

1012
01:35:30.943 --> 01:35:32.278
Good-bye.

1013
01:35:32.695 --> 01:35:33.779
I love you.

1014
01:35:33.862 --> 01:35:35.781
I love you too. Nathalie.

1015
01:37:11.545 --> 01:37:13.130
Florence Norris...

1016
01:37:13.297 --> 01:37:16.467
...I present to you
the Congressional Medal of Honor...

1017
01:37:16.634 --> 01:37:18.886
...the nation's highest decoration.

1018
01:37:20.805 --> 01:37:24.392
Thank you.
but don't you dare let this happen again!

1019
01:37:25.893 --> 01:37:27.645
Richard Norris...

1020
01:37:27.812 --> 01:37:30.815
...on behalf of my parents.
who couldn't be here today...

1021
01:37:30.898 --> 01:37:33.401
...for saving the world from the Martians...

1022
01:37:33.484 --> 01:37:35.987
...I present to you the Medal of Honor.

1023
01:37:36.821 --> 01:37:38.906
Don't kiss me if you don't want.

1024
01:37:39.323 --> 01:37:40.825
I have to.

1025
01:37:43.995 --> 01:37:46.330
I prepared a speech. Is that okay?

1026
01:37:47.081 --> 01:37:49.166
Sure. that's very appropriate.

1027
01:37:54.006 --> 01:37:55.257
Hi. everybody.

1028
01:37:56.675 --> 01:37:57.926
I want to say--

1029
01:37:58.010 --> 01:38:00.596
Can you speak up? We can't hear you.

1030
01:38:01.096 --> 01:38:04.433
I want to say that there's
a lot of people in the world...

1031
01:38:04.516 --> 01:38:07.436
...that have done a lot more
than I have. and...

1032
01:38:07.603 --> 01:38:09.771
...they should be here now...

1033
01:38:10.022 --> 01:38:11.523
...getting a medal.

1034
01:38:13.525 --> 01:38:15.694
And I want to thank my grandma...

1035
01:38:15.861 --> 01:38:18.030
...for always being good to me...

1036
01:38:18.196 --> 01:38:21.116
...and for helping save the world
and everything.

1037
01:38:22.284 --> 01:38:25.537
So. I guess. like. now we just have to...

1038
01:38:25.704 --> 01:38:29.708
...start over and start rebuilding
everything. like our houses.

1039
01:38:29.875 --> 01:38:34.796
But I was thinking. maybe instead
of houses we could live in tepees.

1040
01:38:35.130 --> 01:38:37.299
Because it's better in many ways.

1041
01:38:40.886 --> 01:38:43.555
That's all I have to say. Thanks.

1042
01:38:45.474 --> 01:38:46.725
Was that okay?

1043
01:38:46.808 --> 01:38:47.893
Yeah.

1044
01:38:48.728 --> 01:38:50.438
Do you got a girlfriend?

1045
01:38:50.647 --> 01:38:51.648
No.

1046
01:38:53.066 --> 01:38:56.152
Give me a break.
Go on in there and clean your room.

1047
01:38:56.319 --> 01:38:58.988
I can't do this all by myself. Look at you.

1048
01:40:18.110 --> 01:40:20.195
